data.title: 1963 Chateaugay Horseshoe Presented to Pulitzer Prize Winner Homer Bigart
data.meta_description: This horseshoe from the race horse Chateaugay, who won the Kentucky Derby in 1963 and the Belmont Stakes, was presented to Homer B...
data.text: This horseshoe from the race horse Chateaugay, who won the Kentucky Derby in 1963 and the Belmont Stakes, was presented to Homer Bigart, who was a Pulitzer Prize-winning war correspondent from WWII, and primarily worked for the New York Herald Tribune. Horseshoe is made by the Thoroughbred Race Horse Shoe Company and is a size 5. Very nice presentation metal plaque. Condition is EX-MT.
